<br>
Drakes can be taken out easily by a wizard of 50+<br>
<br>
Here's how (I'm gonna regret this I know):<br>
<br>
prerequisites:<br>
<br>
a. memmed: draught of fire, gate north(or wherever), BoF<br>
<br>
b. Some form of speed (sow or boots)<br>
<br>
creep up BEHIND them. Start casting BoF from OUTSIDE your casting range. Slowly move up and up till you do snare it.<br>
<br>
TURN AROUND AND RUN LIKE A BISH<br>
<br>
Once you're a bit away, keep slamming your draught of fire (all your spells are hotkeyed, right?)<br>
<br>
Nuke, turn and run 5-6 steps away, nuke again. Repeat till dead.<br>
<br>
The trick: Our casting range is significantly greater than that of the drake. What this means is that we can cast and have the spell go off before we trigger their AE.<br>
<br>
If they resist the snare, stay calm. Root it and gate. Come back to fight another day. Do NOT try and run to snare it again. Won't work, and most likely you'll get other people killed.<br>
<br>
I've killed dozens of drakes this way and never got touched once. <p>Zalbar The Mad
Guildmaster Blood Tide</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaspxidar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aspxidar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/7/02 2:08:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=21>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wyverns of CS strats..</span><hr size=1> Bah, I had to dig for this thread because the SEARCH function is disabled.<br>
